net.proteusframework.core.metric

Class Dimension

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.metric.Dimension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, TextSource

    public final class Dimension
extends Object
implements Cloneable, Serializable, TextSource
    The Dimension class is used to specify the width and height of something, normally a component or part thereof. The width and height are specified using Metric objects so that varying units can be used.Instances of this class are immutable.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • Dimension

        public Dimension()
        Create a dimension with no metrics. Internally the width and height fields are null but accessor methods will return a UnknownMetric instance with value 0.

      • Dimension

        height - The height of the Dimension

      • Dimension

        public Dimension(String str)
        Creates a Dimension object from a String. The format is a comma-separated width and height. The width and height values are in the format defined by Metric.valueOf(String).
        Parameters:
        str - The String representation of the dimension.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the String does not specify comma separate width and height Metric values.
        NumberFormatException - If the decimal values are illegal
        See Also:
        Metric.valueOf(java.lang.String)
